SIMPLE: mohammedan
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mohammedan
<hw>Mo*ham"med*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Mohammed</ets>, fr. Ar. <ets>muh⟦aacute⟧mmad</ets> praiseworthy,
highly praised.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Mohammed, or to Islam,
the religion and institutions founded by Mohammed; in the latter sense,
synonymous with <altname>Islamic</altname>, the term preferred by
Moslems.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Mahometan</asp>,
<asp>Mahomedan</asp>, <asp>Muhammadan</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mohammedan</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mohammedan
<hw>Mo*ham"med*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A follower of Mohammed, the
founder of Islam (also called Islamism or Mohammedanism); an adherent of
Islam; one who professes Islam; a Muslim; a Moslem; a Musselman; -- this
term is used mostly by non-Moslems, and some Moslems find it
offensive.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>Muhammadan</asp>,
<asp>Mahometan</asp>, <asp>Mahomedan</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mohammedan calendar</ent>⟦br⟧
